From 067f19ccc3a33fa4019b61a5df8f815adad373ee Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: x <x@x.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 14:35:06 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: renesas: rzv2n-evk: set eth PHY MDIO addr to 2 on
 e1m-x

The RTL8211F-VD PHYs on the e1m-x carrier latch MDIO address 0 (with a
mirror alias at 2) because the PHYAD straps share pins with the MAC RGMII
outputs and lose the strap-vs-MAC contention at reset. At address 0 the
kernel's phy_poll_reset times out (-110, cannot attach); address 2 is the
clean unicast alias where both PHYs attach as stmmac-N:02. The EVK dts
hard-codes reg = <0> (its KSZ9131); move phy0/phy1 to reg = <2> so the
Realtek PHYs attach on this board.

Signed-off-by: Caner <alpcaner92@gmail.com>
---
 .../dts/renesas/r9a09g056n48-rzv2n-evk.dts     | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r9a09g056n48-rzv2n-evk.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r9a09g056n48-rzv2n-evk.dts
index 88c2383b9071..be87e3daafe9 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r9a09g056n48-rzv2n-evk.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r9a09g056n48-rzv2n-evk.dts
@@ -1626,3 +1626,21 @@ usb-ovc-disable-hog {
 		line-name = "usb_ovc_disable";
 	};
 };
+
+/*
+ * ALP e1m-x / v2n-m1: both RTL8211F-VD PHYs latch MDIO address 0 with a
+ * mirror alias at address 2 (the PHYAD straps share pins with the MAC RGMII
+ * RXD3/RXC/RXCTL, so the MAC push-pull outputs contend the weak strap pulls
+ * during the reset-latch window). Address 0 is the broadcast-ish alias where
+ * phy_poll_reset times out (-110, "Cannot attach to PHY"); the clean unicast
+ * alias is address 2, where both PHYs attach as stmmac-N:02 with the RTL8211F
+ * driver. The EVK dts hard-codes reg = <0> (its KSZ9131); move both phy nodes
+ * to reg = <2>.
+ */
+&phy0 {
+	reg = <2>;
+};
+
+&phy1 {
+	reg = <2>;
+};
